<h3><a href="http://besustainable.com/greenmajority/2012/05/25/tgm295-f1/">A Bit of Oates in the Morning</a></h3>
<li>
<p>Lawson Oates, Director of the <a href="http://www.toronto.ca/teo/index.htm">Toronto Environment Office</a> joined the program to talk about urban environmentalism.  Mr. Oates discussed some of the city of Toronto&#8217;s environmental programs as well as talked about managing environmental issues within the political field.</p>
</li>
<p><br clear="all" /><br />
<div id="image_f2" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 200px"><a href="http://www.alternativesjournal.ca/"><img src="http://www.alternativesjournal.ca/sites/default/files/images/covers/38n3ArtCover3D.png" align="left" alt="Alternatives Journal" title="Alternatives Journal" width="190" height="275" class="size-full wp-image-946" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><center><i>Alternatives Journal</i></center></p></div></p>
<h3><a href="http://besustainable.com/greenmajority/2012/05/25/tgm295-f2/">The Alternatives Duo Gets the Word Out</a></h3>
<li>
<p>We here at the show use many sources for our stories and features, but one of our favourites is <a href="http://www.alternativesjournal.ca/">Alternatives Journal</a>.  Alternatives Journal has been around for more than 40 years providing editorials and peer-reviewed articles on a wide range of environmental issues.  We were joined by Eric Ruble the Editorial Manager and David McConnachie the Business Manager for Alternative Journal</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
