		<description><![CDATA[We meet with John Bennet, executive director of the Sierra Club of Canada.  John will talk to us about the BlackOutSpeakOut campaign that is currently underway which has a wide assortment of the biggest environmental NGO's in Canada blacking out their websites on June 4th to protest what he see's as a continuing war on environmentalism by the Federal government.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>You can <a title="This week's second feature" href="http://www.openenvironment.org/audio/TGM_120511_f2.mp3" target="_blank">download this week&#8217;s second feature here</a> or listen in the embedded player.</p>
<div id="image_1" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 218px"><img src="http://openenvironment.org/images/johnbennett.jpg" align="left" alt="John Bennett" title="John Bennett" width="208" height="245" class="size-full wp-image-946" /><p class="wp-caption-text"><center><i>John Bennett</i></center></p></div>
<p>We meet with John Bennet, executive director of the <a href="http://sierraclub.ca/">Sierra Club of Canada</a>.  John will talk to us about the <a href="http://blackoutspeakout.ca/">BlackOutSpeakOut</a> campaign that is currently underway which has a wide assortment of the biggest environmental NGO&#8217;s in Canada blacking out their websites on June 4th to protest what he sees as a continuing war on environmentalism by the Federal government.</p>
<p>You can see the complete episode here: <a href="http://besustainable.com/greenmajority/2012/05/11/tgm-293/">TGM #293 &#8211; No Government Can Take My Bike&#8230; (May 11, 2012)</a></p>
