<div id="image_f1" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 210px"><a href="http://bikechain.utoronto.ca/"><img src="http://sustainability.utoronto.ca/Assets/Sustainability+Digital+Assets/Projects/bikechain/bclogo.gif" align="right" alt="Bikechain" title="Bikechain" width="200" class="size-full wp-image-946" /></a><p class="wp-caption-text"><center><i>Bikechain</i></center></p></div></p>
<h3><a href="http://besustainable.com/greenmajority/2012/05/11/tgm293-f1/">You Never Forget How to Ride a Bike&#8230;</a></h3>
<li>
<p>This week, Toby Bowers director of <a href="http://bikechain.utoronto.ca">Bikechain</a> joins the program.  Bikechain acts as a biking advocacy and outreach group.  Offering a fully equipped bike shop and bike professionals to help students learn to fix their own bikes.</p>
</li>
<p><br clear="all" /><br />
<div id="image_1" class="wp-caption alignleft" style="width: 218px"><img src="http://openenvironment.org/images/johnbennett.jpg" align="left" alt="John Bennett" title="John Bennett" width="208" height="245" class="size-full wp-image-946" /><p class="wp-caption-text"><center><i>John Bennett</i></center></p></div></p>
<h3><a href="http://besustainable.com/greenmajority/2012/05/11/tgm293-f2/">The Government Has Taken Aim&#8230;At Environmentalists?</a></h3>
<li>
<p>We meet with John Bennet, executive director of the <a href="http://sierraclub.ca/">Sierra Club of Canada</a>.  John will talk to us about the <a href="http://blackoutspeakout.ca/">BlackOutSpeakOut</a> campaign that is currently underway which has a wide assortment of the biggest environmental NGO&#8217;s in Canada blacking out their websites on June 4th to protest what he sees as a continuing war on environmentalism by the Federal government.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
